<h2>Comparison: Monitoring Tools vs. Execution Tools</h2>
<p>LLM optimization tools fall into two categories. Understanding the difference is essential for choosing the right platform.</p>
<p><strong>Monitoring tools</strong> track when and where your brand is cited. They answer the question: "Are we visible in AI search?" Profound, Otterly, Ziptie, and theStacc AI Visibility Checker are monitoring tools. They observe, measure, and report.</p>
<p><strong>Execution tools</strong> actively optimize your content for AI citations. They answer the question: "How do we get more visible?" Semrush, Ahrefs, AthenaHQ, Peec, and Scrunch include execution features such as content briefs, optimization recommendations, and automated publishing.</p>
<p>Most teams need both. Monitoring tells you whether your execution is working. Execution creates the visibility that monitoring measures. If your budget allows one tool, choose an execution tool with strong monitoring. Semrush and AthenaHQ fit this description best.</p>
